QUALIFICATION: cited as 'aeneus (var. coeruleus) Donov. Ins. N. Holl. tab. i. (fig. inf. med.)' in Parry, F.J.S. 1864. A catalogue of Lucanoid Coleoptera; with illustrations and descriptions of various new and interesting species. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 3 2: 1-113 (69); the copy of Donovan (1805) available to the authors makes no reference to coeruleus on the plate or in the text; the fig. referred to by Parry as 'inf. med.' is labelled aeneus; the evidence suggests that more than one version of Donovan's 1805 work existed and it is therefore questionable whether Donovan 1805 is a valid publication
